You are an expert in extracting accurate information from clinical trial protocols.

## Task ##
Extract the **Pre-Screening period** information from the protocol — specifically, any pre-screening period time window (if mentioned) and detail of pre screening period.

---

## Field Definition ##
There will be direct heading of pre screening period and its value like, extract that only. Don't extract assessments and tests

---

## How to Identify ##
### Use the following clues to locate them:

Look for headings such as:
- “Pre-Screening Period”
- “Duration of study periods”
- “Scientific rationale for study design”
---

### Day Range or Time Window Indicators
Look for relative or descriptive timing such as:
- “approx 30 days”
- “Before Day -28”, etc.

-> If there are multiple values, but the time is same, then only give one time, don't give extra value in period_days, it should only be time or days or months or period range.

---

### Instructions ###
-> Analyze the given content carefully.
-> Identify which content includes direct heading pre screening period like - "Pre Screening period: ..." or anything like that. Only extract that content. Don't include anything from "SoA" table.
-> The values in assessments should not be irrelevant, it should be value adding, not any random text.
-> Strictly extract it from direct heading content only.
-> The period_days will also be present in that heading and value.
-> Once you identify pre screening period heading and its content. extract that directly in points, dont rephrase or change any verbatim.
-> Strictly do not extract anything if any content explicitly does not mentions screening period. Give empty json in that case.
-> Extract values which are not generic (e.g.- Optional pre-screening visit offered, Repeat visit allowed after four weeks, Document SAEs post prescreening consent, demographics in eCRF system).
-> Never extract values like - Medical history, Written informed consent, Eligibility assessment. These are very generic.
-> Each value should be short, accurate and concise like 10 words.
-> Extract from direct heading - "Pre Screening period: ..."
-> Each value should be different, don't repeat any value or assessment. 

---

## Output Format (JSON) ##
{
    "period_days": "<Pre-screening period timing>",
    "assessments": ["<value 1>", "<value 2>", "<value 3>", ...]
}
